sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client Application
    participant TracerA as Tracer (Client)
    participant Carrier as Carrier (Network)
    participant TracerB as Tracer (Server)
    participant Server as Server Application

    Note over Client, TracerA: 1. Start Span
    Client->>TracerA: StartSpan("Operation A")
    activate TracerA
    TracerA-->>Client: return SpanA
    deactivate TracerA

    Note over Client: 2. Business Logic & Tagging
    Client->>Client: SpanA.SetTag("key", "value")
    Client->>Client: SpanA.Log("event")

    Note over Client, TracerA: 3. Inject Context
    Client->>TracerA: Inject(SpanA.Context, FORMAT, carrier)
    activate TracerA
    TracerA-->>Carrier: Populate carrier with context
    deactivate TracerA

    Note over Client, Server: 4. RPC Call
    Client->>Server: HTTP Request (with carrier)
    activate Server

    Note over Server, TracerB: 5. Extract Context
    Server->>TracerB: Extract(FORMAT, carrier)
    activate TracerB
    TracerB-->>Server: return SpanContextB
    deactivate TracerB

    Note over Server, TracerB: 6. Start Child Span
    Server->>TracerB: StartSpan("Operation B", ChildOf(SpanContextB))
    activate TracerB
    TracerB-->>Server: return SpanB
    deactivate TracerB

    Note over Server: 7. Server Logic
    Server->>Server: SpanB.SetTag("status", "ok")

    Note over Server, TracerB: 8. Finish Span B
    Server->>TracerB: SpanB.Finish()
    
    Server-->>Client: HTTP Response
    deactivate Server

    Note over Client, TracerA: 9. Finish Span A
    Client->>TracerA: SpanA.Finish()
